        <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" expanded="false" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:anchor>2628</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-iii-8.1.15</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>hodge-theory-iii-8.1.15.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
            <fr:authors />
            <fr:number>8.1.15</fr:number>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[K]]></fr:tex> be a DG mixed Hodge <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>-complex.

    
 <html:ol xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
      
 <html:li style="list-style-type: &quot;(i) &quot;">
        With the notation of <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-8.1.10" href="hodge-theory-iii-8.1.10.xml" number="8.1.10" />, <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-8.1.10.1" href="hodge-theory-iii-8.1.10.1.xml" taxon="Variation" number="8.1.10.1" />, and <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-7.1.6" href="hodge-theory-iii-7.1.6.xml" number="7.1.6" />, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(\mathrm {s} K,\delta (W,L),F)]]></fr:tex> is a mixed Hodge <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>-complex.
      </html:li>


      
 <html:li style="list-style-type: &quot;(ii) &quot;">
        We have

        <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>1243</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-iii-8.1.15.1</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-iii-8.1.15.1.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Equation</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>8.1.15.1</fr:number></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[             {}_{\delta (W,L)}E_1^{ab}(\mathrm {s} K\otimes \mathbb {Q})             = \sum _{\substack {\alpha =\gamma -\beta \\b=\alpha +\beta }} \operatorname {H}^\alpha (\operatorname {Gr}_\beta ^W K^{\bullet \gamma })           \tag{8.1.15.1}           ]]></fr:tex></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>

        where the complex <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[({}_{\delta (W,L)}E_1^{\bullet  b},d_1)]]></fr:tex> is the simple complex associated to the double complex of Hodge <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A\otimes \mathbb {Q}]]></fr:tex>-structures of weight <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b]]></fr:tex> given by

        <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>1244</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-iii-8.1.15.2</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-iii-8.1.15.2.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Equation</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>8.1.15.2</fr:number></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[             \small              \begin {CD}               \operatorname {H}^{b-(\beta +1)}(\operatorname {Gr}_{\beta +1}^W K^{\bullet ,\gamma +1}) @>{\partial }>> \operatorname {H}^{b-\beta }(\operatorname {Gr}_\beta ^W K^{\bullet ,\gamma +1}) @>{\partial }>> \operatorname {H}^{b-(\beta -1)}(\operatorname {Gr}_{\beta -1}^W K^{\bullet ,\gamma +1})             \\@. @A{d''}AA @AA{d''}A             \\@. \operatorname {H}^{b-\beta }(\operatorname {Gr}_\beta ^W K^{\bullet ,\gamma }) @>>{\partial }> \operatorname {H}^{b-(\beta -1)}(\operatorname {Gr}_{\beta -1}^W K^{\bullet ,\gamma })             \end {CD}           \tag{8.1.15.2}           ]]></fr:tex></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
      </html:li>


      
 <html:li style="list-style-type: &quot;(iii) &quot;">
        
        On the <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_LE_r]]></fr:tex> pages of the spectral sequence defined by <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(\mathrm {s} K_{A\otimes \mathbb {Q}},L)]]></fr:tex>, the recurrent filtration and the two direct filtrations defined by <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Dec}_1(W)]]></fr:tex> agree;
        similarly, on the <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_LE_r(\mathrm {s} K_\mathbb {C})]]></fr:tex>, the recurrent filtration and the two direct filtrations induced by <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> agree.
        We denoted these filtrations again by <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[W]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> (respectively).
      </html:li>


      
 <html:li style="list-style-type: &quot;(iv) &quot;">
        For <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r\geqslant 1]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[({}_LE_r,W,F)]]></fr:tex> is a mixed Hodge <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>-structure (<fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-0.4" href="hodge-theory-iii-0.4.xml" number="III.0.4" />).
        The differentials <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d_r]]></fr:tex> are morphisms of mixed Hodge <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>-structures.
      </html:li>


      
 <html:li style="list-style-type: &quot;(v) &quot;">
        The filtration <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {H}^\bullet (\mathrm {s} K)]]></fr:tex> is a filtration in the category of mixed Hodge structures, and

        <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>1245</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-iii-8.1.15.3</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-iii-8.1.15.3.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Equation</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>8.1.15.3</fr:number></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[             \operatorname {Gr}_L^p\big ( \operatorname {H}^{p+q}(\mathrm {s} K), \delta (W,L)[p+q], F \big )             = ({}_LE_\infty ^{pq},W,F).           \tag{8.1.15.3}           ]]></fr:tex></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
      </html:li>

    </html:ol></fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
      <fr:backmatter />
    </fr:tree>
    <fr:tree toc="false" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
