      <fr:mainmatter>
        <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" expanded="false" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:anchor>2629</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-iii-8.1.17</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>hodge-theory-iii-8.1.17.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:authors />
            <fr:number>8.1.17</fr:number>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>We now prove <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-8.1.15" href="hodge-theory-iii-8.1.15.xml" taxon="Theorem" number="8.1.15" />.
    Claims (i) and (ii) follow from the fact that
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[       \begin {aligned}         \operatorname {Gr}_n^{\delta (W,L)}(\mathrm {s} K\otimes \mathbb {Q})         &= \sum _{p-q=n} \operatorname {Gr}_p^W\operatorname {Gr}_L^q(\mathrm {s} K\otimes \mathbb {Q})       \\&= \sum _{p-q=n} (\operatorname {Gr}_p^W K^{\bullet  q})[-q]       \end {aligned}     ]]></fr:tex>
    (this isomorphism is compatible with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex>, and we apply <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-8.1.4" href="hodge-theory-iii-8.1.4.xml" taxon="Remark" number="8.1.4" />).
    The proof of <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-8.1.15.2" href="hodge-theory-iii-8.1.15.2.xml" taxon="Equation" number="8.1.15.2" /> is left to the reader.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>Consider the claims:

    
 <html:ol xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
      
 <html:li style="list-style-type: &quot;(aáµ£) &quot;">
        The morphisms <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d_r]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_LE_r(\mathrm {s} K_{A\otimes \mathbb {Q}})]]></fr:tex> are strictly compatible with the recurrent filtration defined by <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Dec}_1(W)]]></fr:tex>.
      </html:li>


      
 <html:li style="list-style-type: &quot;(báµ£) &quot;">
        The morphisms <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d_r]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_LE_r(\mathrm {s} K_\mathbb {C})]]></fr:tex> are strictly compatible with the recurrent filtration defined by <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex>.
      </html:li>


      
 <html:li style="list-style-type: &quot;(cáµ£) &quot;">
        <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_LE_r]]></fr:tex>, endowed with the filtrations considered in (a) and (b) is a mixed Hodge <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>-structure.
      </html:li>


      
 <html:li style="list-style-type: &quot;(dáµ£) &quot;">
        The <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d_r]]></fr:tex> are morphisms of mixed Hodge <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>-structures.
      </html:li>

    </html:ol></fr:p>
            <fr:p>We will prove (a<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_r]]></fr:tex>) and (b<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_r]]></fr:tex>) for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r\geqslant 0]]></fr:tex>, and (c<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_r]]></fr:tex>) and (d<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_r]]></fr:tex>) for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r\geqslant 1]]></fr:tex>, by simultaneous induction.

    
 <html:ol xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
      
 <html:li style="list-style-type: &quot;(A) &quot;">
        <fr:em>Proof of (a<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_0]]></fr:tex>).</fr:em>
        We have
        <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[           \big ( {}_LE_0^{p\bullet }(\mathrm {s} K_{A\otimes \mathbb {Q}}), \operatorname {Dec}_1 W \big )           = (K_{A\otimes \mathbb {Q}}^{\bullet  p}, \operatorname {Dec} W).         ]]></fr:tex>
        By (iv) of <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-8.1.9" href="hodge-theory-iii-8.1.9.xml" taxon="Scholium" number="8.1.9" />, the spectral sequence of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(K_{A\otimes \mathbb {Q}}^{\bullet  p},W)]]></fr:tex> degenerates at <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E_2]]></fr:tex>.
        By <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-ii-1.3.4" href="hodge-theory-ii-1.3.4.xml" taxon="Proposition" number="1.3.4" />, the spectral sequence of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(K_{A\otimes \mathbb {Q}}^{\bullet  p},\operatorname {Dec} W)]]></fr:tex> degenerates at <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E_1]]></fr:tex>, and this proves (a<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_0]]></fr:tex>) (<fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-ii-1.3.2" href="hodge-theory-ii-1.3.2.xml" taxon="Proposition" number="1.3.2" />).
      </html:li>


      
 <html:li style="list-style-type: &quot;(B) &quot;">
        
        <fr:em>Proof of (b<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_0]]></fr:tex>).</fr:em>
        We have
        <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[           \big ( {}_LE_0^{p\bullet }(\mathrm {s} K_\mathbb {C}),F \big )           = (K_\mathbb {C}^{\bullet  p}, F).         ]]></fr:tex>
        We apply (v) of <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-8.1.9" href="hodge-theory-iii-8.1.9.xml" taxon="Scholium" number="8.1.9" /> and <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-ii-1.3.2" href="hodge-theory-ii-1.3.2.xml" taxon="Proposition" number="1.3.2" />.
      </html:li>


      
 <html:li style="list-style-type: &quot;(C) &quot;">
        <fr:em>Proof of (c<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_1]]></fr:tex>).</fr:em>
        We have to show that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {H}^n(K_A^{\bullet  p})]]></fr:tex>, endowed with the filtrations induced by <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Dec} W]]></fr:tex> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {H}^n(K_{A\otimes \mathbb {Q}}^{\bullet  p})=\operatorname {H}^n(K_A^{\bullet  p})\otimes \mathbb {Q}]]></fr:tex> and by <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {H}^n(K_\mathbb {C}^{\bullet  p})=\operatorname {H}^n(K_A^{\bullet  p})\otimes _A\mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex>, is a mixed Hodge <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>-structure.
        But <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Dec} W]]></fr:tex> induces on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {H}^n(K_{A\otimes \mathbb {Q}}^{\bullet  p})]]></fr:tex> the same filtration as <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[W[n]]]></fr:tex>, and so we conclude by (ii) of <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-8.1.9" href="hodge-theory-iii-8.1.9.xml" taxon="Scholium" number="8.1.9" />.
      </html:li>


      
 <html:li style="list-style-type: &quot;(D) &quot;">
        <fr:em>Proof of (c<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_r]]></fr:tex>)+(d<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_r]]></fr:tex>)<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\implies ]]></fr:tex>(a<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_r]]></fr:tex>)+(b<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_r]]></fr:tex>)+(c<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_{r+1}]]></fr:tex>).</fr:em>
        This is the key point of the proof, and is a simple application of <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-ii-2.3.5" href="hodge-theory-ii-2.3.5.xml" taxon="Theorem" number="2.3.5" /> (along with <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-0.4" href="hodge-theory-iii-0.4.xml" number="III.0.4" />).
      </html:li>


      
 <html:li style="list-style-type: &quot;(E) &quot;">
        <fr:em>Proof of (a<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_r]]></fr:tex>)<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_{r\leqslant  r_0-2}]]></fr:tex>+(b<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_r]]></fr:tex>)<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_{r\leqslant  r_0-2}]]></fr:tex>+(c<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_{r_0}]]></fr:tex>)<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\implies ]]></fr:tex>(d<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_{r_0}]]></fr:tex>).</fr:em>
        By <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-ii-1.3.16" href="hodge-theory-ii-1.3.16.xml" taxon="Theorem" number="1.3.16" />, the recurrent filtration and the direct filtrations induced by <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Dec}_1W]]></fr:tex> (resp. <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex>) on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_LE_r]]></fr:tex> agree for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r\leqslant  r_0]]></fr:tex>, and we apply (i) of <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-ii-1.3.13" href="hodge-theory-ii-1.3.13.xml" taxon="Proposition" number="1.3.13" />.
      </html:li>

    </html:ol></fr:p>
            <fr:p>This finishes the proof by induction of (a), (b), (c), and (d).</fr:p>
            <fr:p>Claim (iii) was proven in part (E) of the proof by induction, and the claims of (iv) are (c<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_r]]></fr:tex>) and (d<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_r]]></fr:tex>).
    We will prove <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-8.1.15.3" href="hodge-theory-iii-8.1.15.3.xml" taxon="Equation" number="8.1.15.3" /> in the form of <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-8.1.16.2" href="hodge-theory-iii-8.1.16.2.xml" taxon="Equation" number="8.1.16.2" />.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>The fact that
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[       \operatorname {Gr}_L(\operatorname {H}(\mathrm {s} K_{A\otimes \mathbb {Q}}),\operatorname {Dec}_1W)       = ({}_LE_\infty (\mathrm {s} K_{A\otimes \mathbb {Q}}),W)     ]]></fr:tex>
    follows from (a<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_r]]></fr:tex>) and <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-ii-1.3.17" href="hodge-theory-ii-1.3.17.xml" taxon="Corollary" number="1.3.17" />.
    The fact that
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[       \operatorname {Gr}_L(\operatorname {H}(\mathrm {s} K_\mathbb {C}),F)       = ({}_LE_\infty (\mathrm {s} K_\mathbb {C}),F)     ]]></fr:tex>
    follows from (b<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_r]]></fr:tex>) and <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-ii-1.3.17" href="hodge-theory-ii-1.3.17.xml" taxon="Corollary" number="1.3.17" />.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>We conclude by the following lemma, whose proof is left to the reader:</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
